# Webhook Test Repository

This repository is used to test GitHub webhooks.

## Purpose
The goal of this repo is to verify that webhook events are being sent and received correctly.

## Test Steps
1. Make a change to this file
2. Commit and push to GitHub
3. Check your webhook listener/server
4. Verify that a payload is received

## Sample Change Log
- Initial commit
- Updated README to trigger webhook

## Webhook Events to Watch
- push
- pull_request
- repository

## Notes
If your webhook is working, you should see a JSON payload in your server logs after each push.

